If we can get one—I say every time we do it, if we just get one, wouldn't that be wonderful?

00:43:07.137 --> 00:43:16.879
If we can just get one that was so lost that they just found Jesus tonight.

00:43:16.879 --> 00:43:25.520
If we could just get one for him, but we get 20, and I'm so excited.

00:43:28.640 --> 00:43:28.889
And then we'll get 500 here or a thousand.

00:43:36.000 --> 00:43:37.147
But our whole job is to tell you Jesus loves you and that he has a plan for your life.

00:43:37.147 --> 00:43:41.359
When I tell you these visitations, they're really private for me.

00:43:41.359 --> 00:43:48.400
They're really private for Diana.

00:43:48.400 --> 00:44:08.823
But we become vulnerable so that people can maybe just get a little something, taste and see that the Lord is good, because he's been good to Brandon and Diana.

00:44:08.823 --> 00:44:14.146
When I tell you these angel stories, it's not just me.

00:44:14.146 --> 00:44:41.959
There are other people I know, but I tell you this stuff and I'm very open about it, you know, about the truck going down the road this last time, telling you about how Diana was pregnant with our daughter and God showed up and showed off for us when we didn't have no gas in our truck and the angel of the Lord pushed us to the gas station.

00:44:41.959 --> 00:44:45.566
Those are precious moments, moments that changed Diana and I and the children forever.

00:44:45.566 --> 00:44:48.159
Braden—Megan's still overcoming—but Braden, it changed him forever.

00:44:48.799 --> 00:44:57.720
And it's still so precious when you get a dog raised from the dead.

00:45:09.680 --> 00:45:18.133
And my thing, when I told you all that no matter how much you fast, no matter how much you pray, no matter how much you think yourself righteous after you do that, your righteousness is as filthy rags.

00:45:18.133 --> 00:45:25.058
You are only holy and only able to do what you're able to do by grace.

00:45:25.058 --> 00:45:28.400
It's something you don't earn and something you don't deserve.

00:45:28.400 --> 00:45:31.553
It's grace, ladies and gentlemen.

00:45:32.248 --> 00:45:33.599
That's what I was trying to tell you.

00:45:34.346 --> 00:45:49.660
No matter how much you think you can fast to become ready—and, boy, I tell you what, I fasted, I prayed, I took communion four times today, and I'm qualified to raise the dead.

00:45:49.660 --> 00:45:50.120
It's not about you.

00:45:50.120 --> 00:45:52.551
It's not about how much you are righteous.

00:45:52.551 --> 00:45:53.760
It's about him.

00:45:53.760 --> 00:45:56.788
He became sin for you.

00:45:56.788 --> 00:45:58.571
He became sick for you.

00:45:58.571 --> 00:46:03.749
He became poor for you; through his poverty, through his holiness, he made a way for you.

00:46:03.749 --> 00:46:07.140
No, it wasn't about you and how much you did.

00:46:10.790 --> 00:46:14.280
Because that's what I try to tell you: no matter how holy you think you are, your holiness is nothing compared to what he did.

00:46:14.280 --> 00:46:15.440
He was without sin.

00:46:15.440 --> 00:46:18.286
He became sickness, he became sin for you.

00:46:18.286 --> 00:46:28.319
So, that's what I was trying to get across to you, no matter how much I flipped out that night acting crazy.

00:46:28.319 --> 00:46:34.000
Diana, I tell you, she was there freaking out, thinking, 'I just killed the dog.

00:46:34.000 --> 00:46:37.120
' And then my little girl's going, 'Daddy, just pray.

00:46:37.120 --> 00:46:42.251
' And I'm thinking God is not going to hear me.

00:46:50.410 --> 00:46:50.660
I just flipped out and I'm a total fool right now.

00:46:50.660 --> 00:46:53.673
God, I'm sure he's up there shaking his head going, 'Oh, Brandon.

00:46:53.673 --> 00:47:02.053
' But even in my lowest moment, I was trying to tell you, even in my lowest moment, his grace was enough.

00:47:07.484 --> 00:47:10.922
His mercy is enough.

00:47:10.922 --> 00:47:18.729
Even in your lowest moment—you may be the worst drug addict, alcoholic, gambleraholic, whatever it may be—his grace is enough for you to wash you clean.

00:47:18.729 --> 00:47:22.400
It's something you don't earn and it's something you don't deserve.

00:47:22.400 --> 00:47:24.609
His grace is enough for you.

00:47:31.613 --> 00:47:34.069
You may have the worst sexual problem, and you may be looking at the worst stuff on the internet possible, but his grace is enough for you.

00:47:34.069 --> 00:47:41.691
If you just confess your sins, he is faithful and just to forgive you of your sins and cleanse you of all unrighteousness.

00:47:43.040 --> 00:48:00.800
And that's what I was trying to get across that night: even in my weirdo sin, when I was freaking out and yelling at my kids and acting like a fool, and they're all looking at me going, 'Dad just lost it,' cussing and acting up because I just killed my dog, God showed up and showed off and raised that dog from the dead.

00:48:00.800 --> 00:48:03.737
Even in my moment of embarrassment, his grace is enough for you.

00:48:07.020 --> 00:48:07.280
And he does.

00:48:08.639 --> 00:48:09.279
And what's amazing is it wasn't about a dog.

00:48:09.279 --> 00:48:17.760
Even whenever you say it's him washing your sins, washing your life, making you whole again—do you understand what that takes to get that done?

00:48:17.760 --> 00:48:19.423
No, you don't.

00:48:19.423 --> 00:48:20.959
It was by grace.

00:48:23.135 --> 00:48:23.311
You received by grace through faith.

00:48:26.034 --> 00:48:26.400
You didn't earn it.

00:48:40.187 --> 00:48:40.813
You didn't deserve it.

00:48:40.813 --> 00:48:42.460
But it cost Jesus his life.

00:48:51.200 --> 00:48:51.467
And that's what I was trying to tell you all.

00:48:51.467 --> 00:49:04.549
No matter how much I thought what qualified me—what qualified me, ladies and gentlemen, for raising the dead, casting out devils, doing whatever I got to do to think that I'm qualified today?

00:49:04.549 --> 00:49:11.680
Boy, I tell you what, I haven't cussed in the last 48 hours.

00:49:12.409 --> 00:49:14.529
I haven't done—in fact, Diana and I, we've been acting great together.

00:49:14.529 --> 00:49:17.080
Do you not see that we're doing really good?

00:49:17.080 --> 00:49:18.260
Our marriage is awesome.

00:49:23.430 --> 00:49:28.720
I haven't been cranking her, she hadn't been cranking me, and we're qualified now to go around laying hands on all the people at the churches, and we're going to get everybody healed by the power of God through us because we've done it.

00:49:34.352 --> 00:49:34.720
And I'm telling everybody we're qualified.

00:49:40.180 --> 00:49:42.731
But the moment I looked at her cross and she looked at me crying like, 'Well, why are you being great with me?

00:49:42.731 --> 00:49:44.440
' well, we just disqualified ourselves.

00:49:44.440 --> 00:49:45.589
'God can't use us.

00:49:45.589 --> 00:49:51.933
' Now, that's what the enemy tries to tell you.

00:49:51.933 --> 00:49:55.020
'Well, you know, self-doubt.

00:49:55.020 --> 00:49:58.200
You had a little bit of an anger issue there.

00:50:02.319 --> 00:50:02.652
You're not qualified anymore.

00:50:02.652 --> 00:50:15.850
' That's what I was trying to tell y'all, because he'll always come to try to disqualify you in your own thoughts, to make you second-guess, thinking, 'Well, God's not going to use me, Diana.

00:50:15.850 --> 00:50:16.960
I'm sorry.

00:50:16.960 --> 00:50:24.320
He's not going to use me tonight on YouTube.

00:50:25.537 --> 00:50:32.879
I can't go on there because, you know, I got mad at the guy at the restaurant or whatever.

00:50:32.879 --> 00:50:35.079
' Do you understand?

00:50:46.879 --> 00:50:52.319
The old man's always trying to get back up.

00:51:02.080 --> 00:51:03.280
The old man is always trying to get out of that grave, but you die daily.

00:51:17.839 --> 00:51:23.369
And no matter how much you mess up, his grace is enough for you.

00:51:35.382 --> 00:51:35.851
I'm not saying practice sin and think you can act like a fool all the time—I'm not saying that.

00:51:53.929 --> 00:51:54.200
But if you do mess up, you run to God when you sin; you don't run away from him.

00:52:06.960 --> 00:52:18.560
And there is nobody here that doesn't have some gossip thing going on where you're running and slandering Sister Clipboard, and you're going, 'Well, you know, Sister Clipboard is at church at the hall monitor station over there, and I walked in and she's like, "Well, you're late.

00:52:18.560 --> 00:52:20.834
"' And, boy, she just ticked me off.

00:52:20.834 --> 00:53:02.811
Sister Clipboard was watching, and I came into church today, and she saw I was late, and she's over there being her holy self saying, 'I strode up 30 minutes before church got started, and here you are running in late with your kids trying to put them in children's church, and Sister Clipboard's over there taking note of how many times you come in late on church.

00:53:02.811 --> 00:53:14.560
See, you're not qualified to be the head prayer person at the church this week because you were late five times this last Sunday, or over the last month.

00:53:14.560 --> 00:53:24.920
And so I've been watching, taking note, and I turned it into the pastor, just telling you that you're not ready and you're not qualified.

00:53:24.920 --> 00:53:27.800
' It's the truth.

00:53:27.800 --> 00:53:32.377
And you're always going to have some Sister Clipboard up there doing that.

00:53:32.377 --> 00:53:34.907
It's hall monitor Christians.

00:53:34.907 --> 00:53:36.187
Do you know how many...

00:53:36.187 --> 00:53:37.272
And now I look at...

00:53:39.880 --> 00:53:40.140
You go into a store, they're always looking.

00:53:40.140 --> 00:53:42.480
'I've seen you somewhere, brother.

00:53:42.480 --> 00:53:45.610
' And I'm like, 'I've got to hide myself.

00:53:45.610 --> 00:53:48.068
' I'm just Brandon.

00:53:51.108 --> 00:53:51.302
I just want to go and just pray.

00:53:51.302 --> 00:53:52.559
Well, he showed up late.

00:53:52.559 --> 00:53:53.760
Sister Clipboard's always looking.

00:53:53.760 --> 00:53:56.193
I'm trying to help you all.

00:53:56.193 --> 00:54:00.319
Does that make sense, what I'm trying to say?

00:54:00.319 --> 00:54:03.184
You're never going to get there on your own.

00:54:03.184 --> 00:54:04.064
It's all about Jesus.

00:54:04.064 --> 00:54:07.199
It's all about His blood.

00:54:07.759 --> 00:54:14.210
And Sister Clipboard can put her clipboard up, and you can go in there and just be you and say, 'Jesus, here am I.

00:54:14.210 --> 00:54:15.920
Send me.

00:54:15.920 --> 00:54:18.000
' Either you believe it or you don't.

00:54:18.000 --> 00:54:21.520
But there's always going to be somebody trying to disqualify you, always.

00:54:36.160 --> 00:54:37.839
You know what I get?

00:54:44.080 --> 00:54:53.346
Because I even get people to say, 'You know, I'm done talking bad about you.

00:54:53.346 --> 00:54:56.173
' That's what I got from a brother.

00:54:59.696 --> 00:55:03.840
I say, 'Well, I didn't know you were talking bad about me in the first place.

00:55:03.840 --> 00:55:05.680
I'm not going to ridicule you no more.

00:55:05.680 --> 00:55:10.257
I'm not going to run you down.

00:55:10.257 --> 00:55:12.559
' I say, 'Well, praise God.

00:55:12.559 --> 00:55:15.189
Praise God, brother.

00:55:32.720 --> 00:55:32.880
I'm glad.

00:55:33.360 --> 00:55:36.160
I didn't know that you were talking trash about me in the first place.

00:55:36.160 --> 00:55:40.735
' Well, praise the Lord.

00:55:49.635 --> 00:55:49.839
But you get that and you go, 'Well, I didn't realize you were talking trash about me, but I'm so glad that you're not anymore.

00:55:49.839 --> 00:55:51.911
' But you get what I'm saying?

00:55:51.911 --> 00:55:53.988
'Well, I didn't feel like you're qualified enough.

00:55:53.988 --> 00:55:55.359
' I didn't qualify myself.

00:56:05.988 --> 00:56:06.262
Jesus did.

00:56:06.262 --> 00:56:07.359
I'm just Brandon.

00:56:15.599 --> 00:56:16.755
And He'll use whoever He wants to.

00:56:16.755 --> 00:56:25.302
Does that make sense, what I'm trying to tell y'all?

00:56:25.302 --> 00:56:29.770
There's always going to be somebody behind the scenes saying, 'You're not qualified.

00:56:29.770 --> 00:56:30.898
You're not good enough.

00:56:30.898 --> 00:56:33.280
' 'Well, he didn't go to Bible school.

00:56:33.280 --> 00:56:37.680
He didn't spend five hours praying in the Spirit this morning.

00:56:51.748 --> 00:56:52.022
And I sure didn't see him at the altar crying.

00:56:52.022 --> 00:56:54.800
Unless he shed a couple of tears, he ain't ready.

00:56:54.800 --> 00:56:56.973
' I just say, 'Okay.

00:56:56.973 --> 00:57:08.663
' So, I just try to be real with y'all because I deal with it, too.

00:57:08.663 --> 00:57:10.176
And that's called spiritual Pharisees.

00:57:10.176 --> 00:57:13.040
And they always try to say, 'Who are you?

00:57:13.040 --> 00:57:15.280
Who are you?

00:57:15.280 --> 00:57:17.749
' 'Well, I don't know.

00:57:17.749 --> 00:57:18.498
I'm Brandon.

00:57:20.400 --> 00:57:20.543
I showed up.

00:57:25.164 --> 00:57:25.367
I love you.

00:57:25.367 --> 00:57:32.304
' Well, you know, 'You came to the right place if you were looking for something a little humorous, I guess, but cracking me up.

00:57:32.304 --> 00:57:38.960
' Well, because you do, because you live in it with me, too, and you see what we see.

00:57:45.599 --> 00:57:46.799
And I'm telling you, I am so beyond the political correctness of churchianity and church Pharisaism.

00:57:46.799 --> 00:57:59.673
I've come to tell you that Jesus likes the people who don't have a spiritual ego and just have a...

00:57:59.673 --> 00:58:06.442
'I may have a little dirt on me, but I'm here for you, Father.

00:58:13.520 --> 00:58:16.839
And I may have a little bit of a scrape on my knee, but I love you, Lord, and I just want to help you out.

00:58:16.839 --> 00:58:19.840
' Versus the one that comes in that has the hood on going, 'Oh, I'm here.

00:58:19.840 --> 00:58:20.607
I've been fasting.

00:58:20.607 --> 00:58:21.559
All right, let's pray.

00:58:21.559 --> 00:58:23.439
' Not trying to be funny.

00:58:37.867 --> 00:58:38.293
I'm trying to paint a picture because I'm telling you, you disqualify yourself.

00:58:52.971 --> 00:58:53.280
And I don't know who I'm talking to tonight, but I felt this is for somebody.

00:58:53.280 --> 00:58:54.453
Stop disqualifying yourself.

00:58:56.720 --> 00:58:56.960
You never were good enough in the first place.

00:59:09.218 --> 00:59:09.440
It was always by His grace.

00:59:22.160 --> 00:59:22.409
And His grace is enough for you, lady.

00:59:22.409 --> 00:59:24.400
His grace is enough for you, sir.

00:59:26.720 --> 00:59:27.200
And He loves you.

00:59:46.770 --> 00:59:47.140
And He will polish you up if you stay on that potter's wheel.

00:59:52.559 --> 00:59:53.279
And you'll go, just like I talk about, from glory to glory.

00:59:53.279 --> 00:59:57.646
He's changing us, changing us, changing us.

00:59:57.646 --> 01:00:04.130
His likeness and image to perfect in me, the love of God shown to the world.

01:00:17.680 --> 01:00:17.931
For He's changing, He's changing me from earthly things to the heavenly.

01:00:17.931 --> 01:00:25.359
His likeness and image to perfect in me, the love of God shown to the world.

01:00:25.359 --> 01:00:27.280
Do you understand?

01:00:27.280 --> 01:00:29.245
From glory to glory.

01:00:29.245 --> 01:00:30.891
That's why we sing that.

01:00:30.891 --> 01:00:34.480
From glory to glory, He's changing me, changing me, changing.

01:00:34.480 --> 01:00:38.880
Well, I've got blue hair.

01:00:38.880 --> 01:00:40.079
I've got purple hair.

01:00:40.079 --> 01:00:41.520
I've got pink hair.

01:00:41.520 --> 01:00:43.312
The more, the merrier.

01:00:43.312 --> 01:00:45.680
Let's come on.

01:00:45.680 --> 01:00:51.119
You'll get somebody saved that I couldn't.

01:00:51.119 --> 01:00:53.599
'Well, I got a tattoo over my...

01:00:53.599 --> 01:00:59.627
' You might be able to reach a biker; I couldn't.

01:00:59.627 --> 01:01:00.457
Do you understand?

01:01:00.457 --> 01:01:02.360
Who you can reach, Brandon probably couldn't.

01:01:02.360 --> 01:01:04.640
Who I can reach, you probably couldn't.

01:01:05.359 --> 01:01:06.613
But that's why it's called a body.

01:01:06.613 --> 01:01:09.580
'Well, I got piercings all over me, man.

01:01:09.580 --> 01:01:15.469
I don't even know if they'll even allow me in church.

01:01:15.469 --> 01:01:17.799
' You can come to our church.

01:01:17.799 --> 01:01:18.719
You're here.

01:01:18.719 --> 01:01:19.999
We love you.

01:01:19.999 --> 01:01:23.600
I don't see the way you look.

01:01:23.600 --> 01:01:24.880
I don't care.

01:01:24.880 --> 01:01:30.427
My little girl goes, 'Daddy, I always watch you.

01:01:43.086 --> 01:01:43.280
You always go for the people that are really kind of strange.

01:01:43.280 --> 01:01:49.243
' I said, 'Yeah, baby.

01:01:49.243 --> 01:01:51.079
Yeah, because they're hurting.

01:01:52.119 --> 01:01:54.720
A lot of them are hurting.

01:02:01.943 --> 01:02:02.240
They do that to put on a front to push you away.

01:02:02.240 --> 01:02:04.386
' There's a lot of hurting people.

01:02:04.932 --> 01:02:11.954
And she goes, 'Daddy, you always go to talking to them like that.

01:02:11.954 --> 01:02:19.077
' And I say, 'Yep, because I know they're hurting.

01:02:19.760 --> 01:02:34.831
I make it a point to go to certain Starbucks and get a drink on purpose, even if it's a liberal place, just because it's good ground to get somebody saved.

01:02:43.989 --> 01:02:47.115
And I'll go to the one that I know if I go there, I know they're usually trans.

01:02:51.360 --> 01:02:59.408
And I make it a point every time to try to show Jesus to them and say, God loves you.

01:02:59.408 --> 01:03:07.680
' And they look at you and they go, 'Why are you all so happy?

01:03:07.680 --> 01:03:10.799
Why are you all so happy?

01:03:10.799 --> 01:03:14.697
' 'Because I've got something inside of me.

01:03:14.697 --> 01:03:16.571
He's changed me.

01:03:16.571 --> 01:03:17.828
He's changed me.

01:03:17.828 --> 01:03:19.360
' Do you understand?

01:03:19.360 --> 01:03:25.679
People get mad about that, but where else are you going to get them?

01:03:25.679 --> 01:03:28.274
There's a lot of them.

01:03:32.319 --> 01:03:38.799
I don't go over there beating them in the head with the Bible at Target or any place.

01:03:52.559 --> 01:03:52.986
I just keep showing the love of God to people, and my kids notice it.

01:03:52.986 --> 01:03:55.973
Tip them an extra five bucks.

01:03:55.973 --> 01:04:01.760
'Go buy you a coffee.

01:04:01.760 --> 01:04:03.733
' 'Are you tipping people?

01:04:03.733 --> 01:04:06.079
' Well, my goodness, yes!

01:04:06.079 --> 01:04:09.874
Showing the love of God to folks.

01:04:29.380 --> 01:04:29.770
I do it on purpose.

01:04:30.160 --> 01:04:33.360
I let my light shine before all men.

01:04:38.220 --> 01:04:48.400
And you ain't going to do it by always stiffing people and giving them a quarter and going, 'You know, I'm not tipping you.

01:04:48.400 --> 01:04:51.039
I ain't doing this.

01:04:51.039 --> 01:04:57.920
I ain't going to bless you because you're a little different.

01:04:57.920 --> 01:05:07.099
' And I say, I'm going to love on them, and they're going to look at me like I'm crazy.

01:05:07.099 --> 01:05:13.394
Now, I'm concerned sometime they're going to spit in my food, and I don't like them to know who I am.

01:05:13.394 --> 01:05:19.911
But I'm just being real with y'all, you know, as far as being Brandon on this platform.

01:05:19.911 --> 01:05:22.169
And some of them know now.

01:05:22.169 --> 01:05:24.811
But I always let my light shine.

01:05:24.811 --> 01:05:29.160
And I heard some people say, 'Tell people about Jesus, and then sometimes use words.

01:05:29.160 --> 01:05:32.701
' Sometimes use words, and I just try to show them love.

01:05:32.701 --> 01:05:33.803
Just ooze it.

01:05:33.803 --> 01:05:38.859
Ooze Him everywhere I go, pick up my mail at my post office box.

01:05:38.859 --> 01:05:40.445
They all want to know, 'Who are...

01:05:40.445 --> 01:05:44.079
where are all these people asking for prayer?

01:05:44.079 --> 01:05:49.760
Brandon, who are you?

01:05:49.760 --> 01:05:51.720
' 'I'm a blood-bought, born-again Christian.

01:05:51.720 --> 01:05:54.079
I want to tell you about my friend Jesus.

01:05:54.079 --> 01:05:57.580
Are you sick in your body?

01:05:57.580 --> 01:05:58.020
Yeah.

01:06:14.260 --> 01:06:14.960
Well, let me pray for you.

01:06:14.960 --> 01:06:16.274
' Do you understand?

01:06:25.750 --> 01:06:35.299
I think a lot of people think they have to just be over-religious, passing out tracts and hitting people in the head with it and going, 'Well, you know, you're going to hell, brother.

01:06:35.299 --> 01:06:38.780
' They already know they're going to hell.

01:06:38.780 --> 01:06:40.300
They don't care.

01:06:40.300 --> 01:06:42.719
But what makes you stand out?

01:06:42.719 --> 01:06:44.731
You wear your Christian T-shirt.

01:06:44.731 --> 01:06:46.107
I wear it.

01:06:46.107 --> 01:06:53.600
I try to dress up like Adam Sandler a lot of times, have some neon-looking something on.

01:06:53.600 --> 01:06:59.280
